com.nokia.maps.routing

Interface RouteRequest


  • public interface RouteRequest
    This interface acts as a proxy to the routing service and is responsible for storing the currently selected routes.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Route[] calculateRoute(WaypointParameterList waypoints, Mode mode)
      This method makes a request to the routing service.
      void calculateRoute(WaypointParameterList waypoints, Mode mode, RouteListener listener)
      This method makes an asynchronous request to the routing service.
      void cancelRequest()
      This method cancels any pending asynchronous routing request calculation, and allows a new route to be calculated.

    • Method Detail

      • calculateRoute

        Route[] calculateRoute(WaypointParameterList waypoints,
                     Mode mode)
                       throws java.io.IOException,
                              ServiceError
        This method makes a request to the routing service. The call to Routing service is made synchronously, and therefore blocks further operations until the request is complete.
        Parameters:
        waypoints - the waypoints used to calculate the route
        mode - the mode used during route calculation
        Returns:
        The routes that have been calculated. null may be returned where no route exists.
        Throws:
        ServiceError - on service errors
        java.io.IOException - on I/O errors

      • calculateRoute

        void calculateRoute(WaypointParameterList waypoints,
                  Mode mode,
                  RouteListener listener)
        This method makes an asynchronous request to the routing service. Since the call to the routing service is made asynchronously, it is not blocking.
        Parameters:
        waypoints - the waypoints used to calculate the route
        mode - the mode used during route calculation
        listener - The listener is called back when the result completes asynchronously

      • cancelRequest

        void cancelRequest()
        This method cancels any pending asynchronous routing request calculation, and allows a new route to be calculated.
